MORNING REPORT: MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and international 
news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jorge Mester, music director of the Pasadena Symphony, will conduct the opening 
concert for the new Oakland East Bay Symphony, March 31. The inaugural season 
for the orchestra, which is attempting to fill the void left by the bankruptcy 
of the Oakland Symphony in 1986, lists five concerts through June 3, one of 
them a pops program. The orchestra has raised $120,000 towards its initial 
$360,000 budget, not counting a $100,000 matching grant from the City of 
Oakland. The new ensemble has enlisted 52 of the 72 players from the defunct 
orchestra. 
