<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 KILLED, 1 WOUNDED IN GANG SHOOTINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three more people -- including a teen-age boy -- were killed in three separate 
gang-related shootings on the streets of Los Angeles and Compton, police said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Johnny Kinslow, 15, died at Martin Luther King Jr./Drew Medical Center after he 
and a friend, Johnny Lucien, 14, were shot with a semiautomatic weapon by a 
gunman in a car Wednesday afternoon as they walked along North Dwight Avenue in 
Compton. Lucien was reported in critical condition. 
</P>
<P>
About three hours later, Los Angeles police said, Harold Kenneth, 18, 
identified as a member of the Bloods street gang, was killed at 92nd Street and 
Central Avenue as he walked with his girlfriend. Officers were told that a man 
in a car pulled up and fired several shots from a handgun after saying he was 
going to kill a Blood. 
</P>
<P>
An hour later, Lt. Rob Watters said, shots fired from a stolen car killed Jorge 
Ricky Hernandez, 18, as he walked with friends at Belmont Avenue and Temple 
Street in the Echo Park area. 
</P>
<P>
Officers later arrested a 16-year-old boy as well as Martin Aguilar and Julio 
Escobar, both 18. They were identified as gang members. 
</P>
