<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPRINKLERS DOUSE FIRE ON OIL TANKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Overheated bearing packing in the pumping room of an oil tanker docked at the 
Long Beach Pier sparked a fire Thursday that was quickly extinguished by 
sprinklers aboard the vessel, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of injuries from the fire, but smoke spread through much 
of the tanker, Arco Alaska, causing minor damage, Long Beach Fire Department 
spokesman Bob Caldon said. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators believe that packing around pump bearings overheated and 
triggered a fire in fuel oil, Caldon said. 
</P>
<P>
City firefighters and Coast Guard crews assisted workers aboard the tanker in 
blowing the smoke from the vessel. 
</P>
