<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WROLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The leader of Colombia's most active leftist guerrilla group asserted that 
insurgent groups control one-fourth of that Latin American nation. The claim 
was made in a letter to former President Alfonso Lopez Michelson from Manuel 
Perez, a former Roman Catholic priest who commands the National Liberation 
Army. The letter, published in several Colombian newspapers, was received by 
Lopez on the same day earlier this week that Perez's guerrillas reportedly 
ambushed two river boats in northern Colombia, provoking a clash that killed 10 
servicemen and 20 guerrillas. 
</P>
