<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The founder of Mexico's largest brokerage has declared his innocence on charges 
of illegal trading and criminal fraud following his arraignment at a Mexico 
City prison. "I hope there will be justice. I'm innocent. I believe in the 
Mexican laws," said Eduardo Legoretta, chairman and a founder of Operadora de 
Bolsa, said after being arraigned at the city's Eastern Penitentiary. Legoretta 
and three other top brokerage officials were arrested Monday and later charged 
with illegal trading related to the October, 1987, Mexican stock market crash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
