</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Milwaukee Brewers and six other major league baseball teams will 
participate this year in a study to determine the health effects of smokeless 
tobacco. 
</P>
<P>
The Brewers also were involved last year in the study, which is part of a 
three-year effort by researchers at UC San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
Paul Jacobs, the Brewers' physician, said baseball players make good guinea 
pigs because they are among the most prolific users of chewing tobacco and 
snuff. 
</P>
</TEXT>
