</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The National Football League has fined 16 Denver Broncos a total of $12,500 for 
participating in a brawl during Denver's regular-season finale against the New 
England Patriots in December. 
</P>
<P>
NFL spokesman Peter Abitante said that an undisclosed number of Patriots 
players were fined as well for their roles in the chaotic final minutes of the 
Broncos 21-10 victory at Denver's Mile High Stadium. 
</P>
