<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Valley College basketball team, which forfeited a Western State Conference 
game against Glendale on Wednesday because only four of the team's seven 
players showed up on time, will forfeit its two remaining games. 
</P>
<P>
Valley athletic director George Goff said the decision not to complete the 
season was made after a review of academic records from the first semester, 
which revealed poor attendance and failing grades for several players who would 
have made them ineligible. 
</P>
<P>
Valley was in contention for a spot in the Southern California regional 
playoffs, but the Monarchs conclude the season 17-15 overall and 7-8 in 
conference play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
