<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRVINE WORKS OVERTIME FOR 95-92 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN WEYLER, Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STOCKTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An ailing UC Irvine basketball team limped into Thursday night's game against 
University of the Pacific hoping to find the panacea for all Big West 
Conference teams: Take a win from the Tigers and go to bed. 
</P>
<P>
The Anteaters were playing without Jeff Herdman -- the nation's leading 
three-point shooter who has the flu -- and also had their top rebounder and No. 
2 scorer, center Mike Doktorczyk, limping with a severe thigh bruise. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine, 10-12 overall and 7-6 in the Big West, scored a 95-92 overtime victory 
over Pacific (5-17, 1-12) at the Spanos Center. It was the Tigers' third 
consecutive overtime loss at home. 
</P>
<P>
The Anteaters managed to finally pull away from the tenacious Tigers and led by 
10 (75-65) with 5:33 left in regulation. But Pacific outscored Irvine, 16-2, to 
take a 81-77 lead with 1:25 left. 
</P>
<P>
Doktorczyk, who scored 26 points, hit a three-pointer with 1:13 left to cut the 
Pacific lead to one. After an Irvine turnover -- when guard Kevin Floyd slipped 
to the floor -- Pacific's Reggie Ricks hit a pair of free throws to give the 
Tigers an 83-80 advantage with 20 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
Floyd, who scored 25, then hit a three-pointer with eight seconds left to send 
the game into overtime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
