<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
AGASSI, MAYOTTE AND PERNFORS ARE UPSET LOSERS AT MEMPHIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Johan Kriek, seeded 16th, defeated No. 1-seeded Andre Agassi, 6-7, 7-5, 6-3, 
and unseeded Jimmy Arias upended third-seeded Tim Mayotte, 7-6, 6-7, 7-6, 
Thursday to move into the quarterfinals of the $415,000 Volvo Indoor 
Championship at Memphis, Tenn. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Chang also pulled off an upset, beating fifth-seeded Mikael Pernfors, 
7-5, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
No. 2-seeded Jimmy Connors survived the rash of upsets with a 6-2, 6-2 win over 
South Africa's Pieter Aldrich, and No. 6 Brad Gilbert beat Shuzo Matsuoko of 
Japan, 6-2, 6-0. 
</P>
<P>
John McEnroe celebrated his 30th birthday with a 6-2, 6-3 win over Michiel 
Schapers of the Netherlands to reach the quarterfinals in the $492,500 Stella 
Artois championships at Milan, Italy. 
</P>
<P>
Alexander Volkov of the Soviet union upset fourth-seeded Jakob Hlasek of 
Switzerland, 7-6, 7-5; Slobodan Zivojinovic of Yugoslavia surprised 
sixth-seeded Yannick of France, 7-6, 7-6, and top-seeded Boris Becker beat Guy 
Forget of France, 6-3, 7-6. 
</P>
<P>
Third-seeded Manuela Maleeva of Bulgaria overcame Ann Henricksson, 6-4, 4-6, 
6-3, and moved into the quarterfinals of the $300,000 Virginia Slims of 
Washington at Fairfax, Va. 
</P>
</TEXT>
