<HEADLINE>
<P>
EL CAMINO WILL BATTLE PASADENA IN TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IRENE GARCIA, Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The South Coast Conference basketball tournament starts tonight at El Camino at 
7 when Cerritos (24-4, 5-3), the SCC's second-place team, faces Long Beach 
(18-12, 5-3). The Falcons were upset, 87-84, by third-place Long Beach in the 
SCC finale Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
At 9 p.m. the league champion El Camino Warriors (21-7, 6-2) will play the 
winner of Thursday's Pasadena-Mt. San Antonio game. Mt. SAC is the league's 
last-place team and Pasadena (16-18, 4-4), which has lost twice to El Camino, 
is in fourth. The Warriors finished the regular season with a 91-75 victory 
over Long Beach, and Pasadena ended conference action with a 102-75 win over 
Mt. San Antonio. 
</P>
<P>
El Camino's two league losses were on the road against Long Beach and Cerritos. 
The Warriors were upset by the Vikings, 98-91, in January and lost to Cerritos, 
64-63, at the buzzer Feb. 4. 
</P>
<P>
Tonight's winners will play for the tournament title at 7:30 p.m. Saturday. 
</P>
