<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEART ATTACK MAY HAVE KILLED DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 54-year-old Long Beach man driving on the Garden Grove Freeway apparently 
suffered a heart attack Thursday evening and ran off the road, California 
Highway Patrol officers said. 
</P>
<P>
The motorist died at Westminster Humana Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
He had been driving east approaching the San Diego Freeway when his car left 
the freeway at about 6 p.m., CHP dispatcher Joanne Losenno said. No one else 
was injured in the accident. 
</P>
<P>
The man's name was not immediately released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
