<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CANYON WINS IN 3-A ON HOPE'S GOAL; 
</P>
<P>
COMANCHES EDGE EISENHOWER, 3-2, IN SECOND OVERTIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Steve Hope scored on a header with about 3 minutes left in the second overtime 
to give Canyon High School a 3-2 victory over Eisenhower in a Southern Section 
3-A boys' first-round soccer match Thursday at Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
Eisenhower's Mike Lehman scored with about 8 minutes left in regulation to tie 
it at 2-2. Steve Kerr and Fred Velez had scored for Canyon as the Comanches 
took a 2-0 lead in the second half. Juacquin Webb scored Eisenhower's other 
goal. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Snitko had six saves for Canyon (16-2-5). Eisenhower ends its season 
7-8-6. 
</P>
<P>
In other 3-A matches: 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo 2, Foothill 0 -- Damon Hubbart scored in the first half and Ryan 
Darke in the second half for host Mission Viejo (22-3), the top-seeded team and 
the South Coast League champions. Foothill finishes 4-6-6. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 5, Millikan 0 -- Francisco Chavez scored three goals to lead host 
Santa Ana (18-1-6), the Century League champions. Marco Silva and Gus Plasencia 
also scored for Santa Ana. Hector Romas had four saves for Santa Ana, the 
playoffs' third-seeded team. Millikan finishes 12-9-1. 
</P>
<P>
In 1-A boys' soccer matches: 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 3, Sunny Hills 0 -- Miguel Ochoa scored three goals for host 
Saddleback (11-6-3), the Sea View League champions. Sunny Hills ends its season 
10-6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Artesia 3, Newport Harbor 2 (sudden death) -- Bryan Mallin and Tommee Walker 
scored for visiting Newport Harbor (9-7-5). 
</P>
</TEXT>
