<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH UPSETS TUSTIN IN 4-A 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tara Snyder scored in the first half to lead Huntington Beach High School to a 
1-0 upset of Tustin in a Southern Section 4-A girls' soccer match Thursday at 
Tustin. 
</P>
<P>
Gina Corbin had six saves for Huntington Beach (9-10-4), the third-place team 
from the Sunset League. The Oilers, who have never before advanced past the 
first round, will play Simi Valley in the second round Tuesday. Lisa Templeton 
had six saves for Tustin (11-5-3), the Sea View League champions. 
</P>
<P>
In other 4-A first-round matches: 
</P>
<P>
Edison 2, Torrance 1 -- Alysson Gibbs scored with about 7 minutes left to break 
a 1-1 tie for host Edison (9-8-5). Torrance led, 1-0, at the half but Amy Lund 
tied it for Edison early in the second half. Nikki Turner had seven saves for 
Edison. Torrance ends the season (14-5-2). 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley 4, El Dorado 0 -- Susan Staab, Ginger Frank, Becky Linhart 
and Sarah Stoney scored for the second-seeded Cougars (18-4-2) at home. 
</P>
<P>
Chaffey 3, University 1 -- Host Chaffey (18-5-2) scored three first-half goals 
and advances to played top-seeded Esperanza Tuesday in the second round. 
</P>
<P>
Palos Verdes 1, Marina 0 (OT) -- Palos Verdes scored in the second overtime to 
upset Marina, the Sunset League champions. Palos Verdes, an at-large team from 
the Bay League, is 12-10-1. Marina finishes 12-7-4. 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar 2, Los Alamitos 1 (OT) -- Julie Smith scored the winning goal on 
a header off a corner kick by Katy Gie at the 6-minute mark of overtime. Corona 
del Mar goalie Kim Kolstad made a diving save with about 30 seconds left in 
regulation to force the overtime. Tracy Schriber scored the first goal for 
Corona del Mar (16-5-4), and Laura Brun converted a penalty kick with 7 minutes 
remaining in regulation for Los Alamitos (15-7-2) to tie the score. 
</P>
<P>
Dana Hills 3, West Torrance 0 -- The Dolphins (16-5-5) got goals from Stacy 
Juhl, Heidi Phillips and Jenny Koenig. Dana Hills goalie Karla Gunderson had 
four saves, and Brigit Tapp had 12 saves for West Torrance (15-5-5). 
</P>
<P>
In a 2-A first-round match: 
</P>
<P>
Valencia 2, Ganesha 0 -- Kristina Yoseloff scored a goal in each half for host 
Valencia (17-6), the Orange League champions. Ganesha finishes the season 
13-6-3. 
</P>
