<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LONG BEACH WOMEN ROLL PAST TITANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Penny Toler scored 18 points to lead Cal State Long Beach to a 71-54 victory 
over Cal State Fullerton in a Big West Conference women's basketball game 
Thursday at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
It was the 38th consecutive conference victory for Long Beach, the ninth-ranked 
team in the nation. 
</P>
<P>
Cheryl Dowell scored 12 points and Angelique Lee and Traci Waits scored 11 each 
for Long Beach (21-4 overall, 13-0 in conference play). Lee led Long Beach with 
10 rebounds and Dowell had 7. 
</P>
<P>
Kathy Werth scored 13, Felica Benson 12 and Jill Matyuch had 10 for Fullerton 
(18-6, 10-5). Belson led the Titans with 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton was plagued by poor shooting, making only 23 of 59 shots (39%). Long 
Beach hit on 33 of 73 (45%). 
</P>
<P>
In California Collegiate Athletic Assn. women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 78, Cal State Northridge 69 -- Kim Riff and Julie King scored 20 points 
each to lead the Panthers (11-11, 7-3) at Chapman. The Panthers shot 51% from 
the field compared to 37% for Northridge (17-7, 5-4). Jackie Saunders had 10 
rebounds for Chapman. Julie Arlotto scored 21 points for Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
In the national Christian College Athletic Assn. Division II regional men's 
playoffs: 
</P>
<P>
Pacific Christian College 115, Life Bible 41 -- Mike DeVries scored 25 points 
and Mike Vincent added 22 to lead Pacific Christian in a first-round game at 
Valencia High School. 
</P>
</TEXT>
