<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
WOMAN'S BODY FOUND IN CAR TRUNK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The body of a prominent Seal Beach real estate agent was found shot to death 
and stuffed into the trunk of her Mercedes-Benz in Long Beach, authorities said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Arlene Lee Chee, 46, was last seen alive leaving her Century 21 office at noon 
Wednesday for an appointment with another real estate agent, Detective Ron 
Pavek said. Her body was found about 9:50 p.m. Thursday in the trunk of her car 
parked in a residential neighborhood at 25th Street and Fashion Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Chee's husband reported her missing Thursday morning when she did not return 
home. About 30 family members and friends searched for Chee on Thursday before 
her brother spotted her Mercedes, Pavek said. 
</P>
<P>
Pavek said Chee had probably been shot sometime before Wednesday night. Her 
purse was missing, but detectives do not believe that robbery was a motive 
because her jewelry was found still on her. 
</P>
</TEXT>
