<P>
OUSTED DICTATOR'S KIN FLY TO MIAMI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ASUNCION 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The wife and daughter of ousted Paraguayan dictator Alfredo Stroessner flew to 
Miami where they could take up permanent residence, a government official said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Ligia Mora, her daughter, Graciela, and Graciela's second husband, Spaniard 
Manuel Gonzalez Llama, left Asuncion Thursday night on a regular flight to 
Miami, presidential secretary Conrado Pappalardo said. "Nobody bothered them, 
they never had any problems here in Paraguay, nor were they detained." 
</P>
</TEXT>
