<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
NORTH TRIAL TO BEGIN TUESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Iran-Contra trial of Oliver L. North has been set to begin Tuesday morning, 
officials at the U.S. Courthouse said today. 
</P>
<P>
Problems have been worked out over the use of classified material that North 
wants to introduce in his defense, and U.S. District Judge Gerhard A. Gesell is 
telling the jury to report at 9:30 a.m. Tuesday, said the officials, speaking 
on condition of anonymity. 
</P>
<P>
A jury of nine women and three men was chosen Feb. 9, the same day the Justice 
Department began trying to delay the trial. The department lifted its 
objections Wednesday after receiving assurances from independent counsel 
Lawrence E. Walsh, whose office is prosecuting North, that classified material 
would be protected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
