<HEADLINE>
<P>
PADRES WIN TERRELL ARBITRATION CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An arbitrator ruled today in favor of the San Diego Padres in the arbitration 
case involving pitcher Walt Terrell. 
</P>
<P>
Terrell, who was acquired during the off-season from the Detroit Tigers, will 
earn $775,000 this year, rather than the $941,000 he requested. 
</P>
<P>
The hearing was held Thursday before arbitrator Richard Kasher. Arguing on 
behalf of the Padres was Tal Smith, who will be the Padres' acting general 
manager on a temporary basis beginning Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
