<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
EXPOS' PEREZ IN DRUG PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MONTREAL 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pitcher Pascual Perez of the Montreal Expos, who has had previous problems with 
substance abuse, has been in a drug rehabilitation center for the last two 
weeks, the National League team said today. Perez entered the center in Florida 
after meeting in his native Dominican Republic with David Dombrowski, the 
Expos' vice president of player personnel. 
</P>
<P>
The club said Perez had failed to comply with a strict after-care program 
prescribed by doctors because of previous drug-abuse problems. Perez, a 
right-hander, had a 12-8 won-lost record, with a 2.44 earned-run average in 188 
innings pitched last season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
