<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
RACING STEWARD GERARD BURKE DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gerard Burke, until recently the steward for the New York Racing Assn., died in 
his sleep Thursday night at his home in Bellmore, N.Y. He was 62. Burke was 
appointed NYRA steward in 1979 after serving as steward for the New York State 
Racing and Wagering Board. He is survived by his wife, Pat, and two sons. 
Funeral arrangements were incomplete. 
</P>
</TEXT>
